The paper deals with the dynamic version of the classic set cover problem, which is a fundamental problem in combinatorial optimization and falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and lower bounds, which are topics in theoretical computer science and computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper mentions primal-dual algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper uses the distributed PCP-framework, which is a topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
